subject: Re: [junit] validate() and reset()

messageBody:
A few thoughts:

1. What have you tried so far? What obstacles have you come up against that
make you ask us this question?

2. In my opinion, this isn't something that can break. Instead I would test
the super class implementation. On that same note, why do you even have
these methods here? Are you opening up the access level (from default or
protected to public)?

- Jason

On Monday 10 January 2005 07:12, computing_skills wrote:
> I have a two methods (see below) and would like to get some guidance
> on how to test for them.
>
>   public void reset(ActionMapping mapping, HttpServletRequest
> request)
>   {
>     super.reset(mapping, request);
>   }
>
>   public ActionErrors validate(ActionMapping mapping,
> HttpServletRequest request)
>   {
>     return super.validate(mapping, request);
>   }
